abstract = {The problem of renormalization of gauge fields is studied. It is observed that the use of non-gauge invariant regulator fields is not excluded provided that in the limit of high regulator mass gauge invariance can be restored by means of a finite number of counter-terms in the Lagrangian. Massless Yang-Mills fields can be treated in this manner, and appear to be renormalizable in the usual sense. Consistency of the method is proved for diagrams with non-overlapping divergencies by means of gauge invariant regulators, which however, cannot be interpreted in terms of regulator fields. Assuming consistency the S-matrix is shown to be unitary in any order of the coupling constant. A restriction must be made: no local, parity-changing transformations must be contained in the underlying gauge group. The interactions must conserve parity.}
